-- Hungary May Lower Phone-Call Tax Limit in 2012, Portfolio Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-05-24T11:50:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/hungary-may-lower-phone-call-tax-limit-in-2012-portfolio-says.html
Hungary may lower the upper limits of
a recently approved tax on phone calls in 2012, news website
 Portfolio  reported today, citing amendments submitted by
lawmakers.  Under the proposed changes, the maximum monthly charge for
individual customers would be 400 forint, compared with the
approved 700 forint per subscription, and for companies it would
be 1,400 forint versus 2,500 forint per subscription, Portfolio
said.  Hungary will introduce the phone-call tax as of the start
of July. The lower limits would be in effect only until the end
of 2012, according to the website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
